rComments: Amazing Professor!!!

Professor Saadi is not only an excellent professor but also a mentor who will change your opinions on Finance. He sets an example for every professor at the university, and everyone should learn something from him. He is absolutely amazing and knowledgeable. More importantly, he treats every student as an individual instead of a number. TAKE HIM!

Someone gives this prof a promotion! He truly cares about students and he reduces the heavy workload so that we can pay attention to other classes. Among all the courses I have taken this online semester, he is the only prof who makes the course easier than it used to be. Choose this prof, he is JESUS reincarnation!!!

I took ADM3750 (in French) over the summer 2020. It was my first online course and I wasn't sure how to study for it! I was very fortunate to have Prof. Saadi. He was caring, patient and explained the materials in a creative way. I'm now taking his M&A course and I continue to enjoy his teaching approach. He's my favorite finance Prof so far!

This prof is hardly accessible with the online course. Often, I have to go through the faculty to get an email answer from him. He's putting a ton of trap in the exam just to make sure you fail it. Then, after the exam he's unwilling to discuss about it and he can only repeat to you : "I'm very generous with your points (stop bordering me)".
B EST FINANCE PROF EVER!

Loved this prof. His lectures are great and he takes his time explaining all the material clearly to make sure everyone understands. His exams are super straight forward. Hands down my favourite prof at Telfer.
Amazing Professor
Dr. Saadi is an amazing finance professor. He's a genius who knows exactly what it takes to convey complex materials to his students. Just watch out for his exams as they can be very tricky!

Very nice professor who genuinely cares about his students. His classes are very interesting and his lectures stimulating, its very easy to follow and participate. Take good notes in his class, he puts a lot of trick questions on the final.
Very respected and great prof... beware of his exams and actually listen to what he says and take detailed notes
he's a very good prof but his exams are tricky ... make sure to attend all his lectures and take detailed notes

Prof Saadi keeps the lectures entertaining and actually keeps your interest. Buy the book and read before every class, it really helps! Also, pay attention in class because there will be questions on small details said only in class. I'm doing the financial math and economics program, and he is one of the best profs.

Highly recommended. Very friendly and easy to approach. He makes complex materials and mathematical proofs easy to follow and understand. Take detailed notes if you want to do well in his theory course
Says we can have some stuff on our cheat sheet and day of the final exam tells you to erase most of it...

Great Prof for Finance Theory. Really cares about his students and how they do. He will take the time to explain things to you. Tries his best to make the class as enjoyable as possible. Mid-term and final exams were tricky so study hard.
His exams are very tricky. Make sure you take extensive notes in class. Other than that he's a very good teacher and easy to approach.
My favorite finance professor at Telfer. Excellent teacher with a big heart. Had a major impact on my career choice!

Dr. Saadi is an amazing finance professor!!! I love the way he teaches the finance theory course, a very tough course by the way. He continuously links theory to practice using very recent examples from real world. Exams are fair but tricky though. Make sure you take extensive note in his lectures. I wish he is teaching other courses too!
His exams are hard and tricky but he's a great teacher... don't skip classes if you want to pass!
Dr. Saadi is the best finance professor at Telfer, Period!
His by far my favorite finance professor! Highly knowledgeable, excellent lecturer and you can sense that he is a good person with a big heart. His exams are a bit tricky but fair.
He is an amazing teacher and very nice person!  Final exam was tough, but fair.  I wish he was teaching other undergraduate courses  :-(

Great Teacher! Really wants you to do well. But you won't get an Easy A in this class, not much guidance for the midterm/final, so they can be tricky.  He really likes to test you on things he talked about in class, so make sure you take notes, especially for the  final.

Prof. Saadi is simply the best finance professor I've ever had. he is highly knowledgeable and makes you love finance !  We are  introduced to the latest developments in finance research and he constantly links  finance theory to practice.
He's a good teacher and really cares about student, but often goes off topic. It's hard to know what's important or not for exams. Too much material to remember, despite the cheat sheet.

By far the best professor I have had at Telfer. Really cares about his students and goes in depth on subject matter to ensure understanding. Make sure you go to class because he often gives students chance to hand in solutions to in class problems for bonus on midterm. Content on midterm was very fair, but multiple choice was a bit tricky.
The most respected and popular finance prof at Telfer and even in the capital region!

Dr. Saadi was BY far the BEST finance professor I have ever had. He was my finance prof ONLINE and he still takes the cake as the most helpful, intelligent and caring professor even though it was online. He takes genuine interest in the well being of his students as long as you show your own dedication to learning.

Prof. Saadi est le meilleur Prof de finance à Telfer!  Le cours est aussi excellent pour ceux qui aiment la finance. mais le manuel utilisé dans le cours est tres dense et plate ... une traduction de l'anglais :(
Excellent Prof.
Best finance Prof. at Telfer!  Best researcher as well!  Midterm exam was fair but final was tough!!! You have to work hard in this course if you are aiming for an A or A+

Professor Saadi makes you love finance even if you're a marketing major. Very enthusiastic. It is clear that he loves teaching and helping his students. You never get bored in his lectures, BUT you have to put in a lot work to get a decent grade.. . he is always there to help you though!   In my opinion,he's a rising star at Telfer
This prof is a game changer! Though I ended up with a B+ ( I was hoping for an A at least), I think he's by far the best professor I've ever had.

Professor Saadi is very straightforward. His lectures are decent and he can be very funny at times he also goes off on many tangents that aren't necessary for the course but are interesting if you want to learn about finance. The midterm and final were mostly based off of the HW and assignments in class, write EVERYTHING on your cheatsheet   A+

Good lecturer however he often goes off topic and in depth into things we don't need to know for the course. Short Answer questions on the Midterm and Final were from the practice problems provided or the Assignments. Do readings thoroughly as the multiple choice are tricky.
